4. Business Opportunity
4.1. Market demand
The strong development of CTF (Capture The Flag) in the cybersecurity field has created large demand for platforms to organize CTF competitions in a stable, secure and scalable way. CTF has now become an important tool in evaluating, researching and developing cybersecurity personnel at educational institutions. For participants, CTF competitions serve as an excellent foundational step for pursuing a career in cybersecurity and information safety field (According to the CỔNG THÔNG TIN ĐIỆN TỬ HỌC VIỆN ANND4. At FPT University, the annual FPTU SecAthon - large-scale CTF event - is setting increasingly high requirements for technical infrastructure serving competitions. With long competition time, increasing number of teams and contestants, as well as the complexity of challenges, the CTF competition platform needs to be comprehensively upgraded to fully meet the organizers’ requirements on stability, security and high load handling. This urgent demand stems from the reality that the current system still has weaknesses in architecture, security and user experience, which need to be overcome to ensure the competition takes place successfully and professionally.
4.2. Target customers
The target customer group of F-CTF is determined based on the need to organize cybersecurity competitions in the market, including three main groups:
First are educational institutions, especially universities, academies and colleges that have training or orientation in the field of information security and information technology. This group has the need to use the CTF platform to organize academic competitions, technical playgrounds and activities to evaluate student capabilities in the cybersecurity field.
Second are academic clubs and student communities in cybersecurity. This is the group of users that regularly organizes internal CTF competitions on medium and small scales, with high requirements on flexibility, challenge customization capability and reasonable operation costs.
Third are organizations, enterprises and units operating in the cybersecurity field. These units can use F-CTF to organize professional competitions, personnel selection programs or internal capability evaluation activities in the cybersecurity field.
4.3. Competitive value
The core competitive value of F-CTF lies in solving the limitations of current platforms. While systems such as CTFd or GZ::CTF meet basic competition needs, they are often limited in limiting the number of challenge instances that can run simultaneously for each team, or incur quite large copyright costs.
The F-CTF system is built separately, optimized for real competition environments. With advantages such as deep customization settings, allowing organizers to self-decide the number of instances running simultaneously, along with infrastructure design towards zero downtime.
In addition, the interface and functions are customized to ensure organizers can quickly detect and handle incidents during competitions thanks to centralized logging and management. Compared to expensive commercial solutions, F-CTF provides complete control and customization in technology, data and operation processes, ensuring absolute transparency and technological autonomy for the school.
Besides the technical factor, the system also brings competitive value in terms of brand identity when designed according to the distinctive identity of FPT University. This not only enhances user experience but also contributes to building a professional image of the school in the cybersecurity community.
4.4. Expansion potential
F-CTF has high expansion potential thanks to flexible architecture and ability to deploy in many different environments. The system can be applied to many organizations and units that need to organize large-scale cybersecurity competitions and can also aim for cooperation with management agencies or professional associations to expand the organization’s scope. In the enterprise sector, F-CTF can be applied to many large organizations and companies, not only in the technology field but also in industries such as finance, banking or fields with high requirements for system security, serving the organization of internal capability evaluation competitions or professional events. In addition, the system could develop according to the global SaaS service model with multi-language and multi-region support, allowing provision of the CTF organization platform for international customers and expanding operation scope to the global market.
5. Software Product Vision
5.1. Vision 
The product vision is to build a stable, secure and scalable Capture The Flag (CTF) platform, specially designed for organizing the annual FPTU SecAthon competition at FPT University. The system aims to become the most reliable and professional CTF organization platform for this large-scale competition, ensuring a fair, transparent and high-quality competition experience for all participating contestants. The product plays the role of a professional CTF organization tool, where competing teams can compete with high-quality challenges in a safe and stable competitive environment.
5.2. Core values
The core values that FCTF brings are built on the following pillars:
●	Stability and reliability: The system ensures stable operation throughout the competition time, even in competitions lasting many hours or days, with minimized downtime. Multi-layer security mechanisms are deeply integrated into the system architecture to prevent forms of cheating, sabotage attacks or unauthorized exploitation during the competition. Access management, session control and user behavior monitoring are performed tightly to ensure fairness and safety for the entire competition. In addition, the centralized administration interface combined with a comprehensive logging system allows the operation team to monitor system status in real time, quickly detect and handle arising incidents. This contributes to maintaining a professional, stable and reliable competition experience for all participating contestants.
●	Flexible scalability: The system could adapt to different usage scales, allowing each team to deploy multiple challenge instances in parallel without affecting overall performance. For large-scale competitions such as SecAthon, F-CTF has strong scalability to handle a large number of simultaneous access requests, with many challenge instances deployed in parallel in a short time. The system architecture allows flexible resource allocation and recovery, ensuring stable performance even when load increases suddenly.
●	Ease of use and user-friendly: One of the outstanding values of F-CTF is the ability to provide an intuitive and friendly usage experience for all participants. The system interface carries the distinctive identity of FPT University and is optimized for different user groups. For contestants participating in the competition, operations such as accessing challenges, deploying instances and submitting flags are designed simply, clearly and easy to understand. The system aims to minimize technical barriers, allowing contestants to focus on solving challenges instead of encountering difficulties in using the platform. For organizers, administration tools are designed in an intuitive and consistent direction, supporting competition configuration, user management and progress tracking effectively, ensuring the competition proceeds smoothly.
5.3. Target audience
The target audience of F-CTF is determined based on usage roles in the system:
The first group is students and CTF contestants. This is the central user group of the system, including students of any year at university studying subjects related to information security, as well as contestants passionate about the CTF subject nationwide. F-CTF helps provides a platform for participants to practice with real simulated situations, allowing experimentation, making mistakes and learning from the process without worrying about accidentally damaging the real system or violating security regulations, helping participants improve their level and practical capability.
The second group is organizers and technical operation teams. Organizers and technical operation teams are the group responsible for deploying, monitoring and ensuring the system operates stably throughout the contest or teaching activities. For this group, administration tools, real-time system status monitoring and user support are key factors. F-CTF provides the ability to track the status of challenge instances, early detection of performance or security incidents, as well as support for quick handling of arising issues during the competition. A well-designed platform with an operator perspective will contribute to ensuring the continuity, fairness and professionalism of the entire event.
5.4. Product objectives
The main objective of F-CTF is to build a professional, stable and reliable Capture The Flag organization platform for the annual FPTU SecAthon competition. One of the core objectives of F-CTF is to provide contestants with a professional and fair competition environment, allowing teams to solve cybersecurity challenges in many different fields. The system aims to ensure stability, security and high load handling capability throughout the competition time, while providing effective administration tools for organizers to monitor, supervise and handle incidents promptly. Through this, F-CTF contributes to improving the quality of the competition and building the reputation of the SecAthon event in the cybersecurity community.
