The long-term orientation of F-CTF focuses on building a sustainable and professional CTF organization platform, playing the role of core infrastructure for the annual SecAthon competition of FPT University. In addition, through organizing the SecAthon competition with increasingly higher quality, F-CTF contributes to the development of the cybersecurity community at FPT University. The competition creates opportunities for outstanding students to demonstrate their skills and knowledge in a real competition environment. Data and achievements from the competition can be used as a basis to identify and select talents for professional competition teams, contributing to enhancing the position of FPT University in the cybersecurity field.
6. Project Scope & Limitations
6.1. In Scope
The F-CTF project focuses on overcoming limitations and weaknesses in the architecture and operation process of the current system, while upgrading core components to improve stability, security, processing performance and user experience. The following main improvements and features are included in the scope to ensure high readiness, good usage experience and practical value:
●	Deploying ChallengeGateway to control challenge access: Building an intermediate gateway acting as the only entry point from the outside to challenge backends, overcoming the problem of directly exposing network ports and preventing unauthorized access between challenges.
●	Improving the Health Check mechanism in challenge deployment: Applying readiness probe to ensure the connection string is only returned when the service is truly ready to serve requests.
●	Enhancing challenge template isolation and security mechanism: Redesigning the challenge deployment template with sandbox runtime, Pod Security Standards, NetworkPolicy and minimum privilege constraints to limit the impact scope of challenges on the system.
●	Enhancing the stability of the challenge deployment process: Improving the mechanism for handling challenge environment initialization requests through control plane isolation, configuring resource and timeout for workflows, and establishing resource priority mechanism to avoid workflow hanging or deadlock.
●	Optimizing system performance and improving source code quality: Refactoring some backend components to eliminate anti-patterns such as N+1 query and incorrect DI lifetime configuration. At the same time standardizing code architecture, applying centralized error handling mechanism and switching from polling model to event-driven monitoring using Kubernetes Informer/Watcher to reduce load on API Server and improve system response capability. Implementing multi-layer path control in the challenge file download function: overcoming the path manipulation vulnerability allowing contestants to arbitrarily access directories in NFS mount.
●	Improving management experience and operation process: Upgrading the administration interface with optimized search, filter and pagination functions for user, team, challenge and submission management modules. Adding operation support tools such as challenge data analysis dashboard, Reward Query module to serve awards and batch data import/export mechanism.
●	Improving system activity monitoring and tracing capability: Upgrading the Monitoring and Log page with filtering functions by team, user, instance status and challenge type, and supporting real-time log updates. In addition, implementing administration modules such as Instance History, Audit Log and Action Log to record activity history and support incident tracing during operation.
●	Implementing multi-layer path control in the challenge file download function: Overcoming the path manipulation vulnerability allowing contestants to arbitrarily access directories in NFS mount by implementing four independent control layers.
●	Building automated CI/CD process for system deployment: Deploying a complete CI/CD pipeline based on GitHub Actions organized into four stages of change detection, parallel build, automatic deployment and result checking, helping to shorten the deployment process from many manual steps down to one git push operation.
6.2. Out of Scope
Due to the specific characteristics of each challenge type, the Dynamic Flag mechanism cannot be applied to the entire system and is outside the general implementation scope of this version.
